{
  "texts": [
    "LLMs' brittleness in math reasoning.",
    "The fragility of LLMs in mathematical reasoning is evident across three dimensions.",
    "Firstly, when presented with questions expressed in varying textual forms (comprising words and numbers), LLMs exhibit inconsistent performance.",
    "Secondly, for identical questions, an LLM may yield different final answers through distinct reasoning paths during multiple trials.",
    "Lastly, pre-trained math-oriented LLMs are susceptible to attacks from adversarial inputs, highlighting their vulnerability in the face of manipulated data."
  ]
}